1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,641
We've got tons of laws to protect the public against hundreds of body poisons.

2
00:00:00,991 --> 00:00:06,641
We put, or should put, poisons on the top shelves so the kids can't reach them.

3
00:00:06,911 --> 00:00:12,000
We go to any extreme to avoid body poison, and it's good that we do.

4
00:00:12,591 --> 00:00:20,000
But there's another type of poison, perhaps a little more insidious, thought poison, commonly called gossip.

5
00:00:20,271 --> 00:00:24,081
Thought poison differs from body poison in two ways.

6
00:00:24,271 --> 00:00:28,240
It affects the mind, not the body, and is more subtle.

7
00:00:28,511 --> 00:00:31,681
The person being poisoned usually doesn't know it.

8
00:00:32,431 --> 00:00:36,480
Thought poison is subtle, but it accomplishes big things.

9
00:00:36,591 --> 00:00:42,960
It reduces the size of our thinking by forcing us to concentrate on petty, unimportant things.

10
00:00:43,231 --> 00:00:49,521
It warps and twists our thinking about people because it is based on a distortion of facts,

11
00:00:49,631 --> 00:00:55,521
and it creates a guilt feeling in us that shows through when we meet the person we've gossiped about.

12
00:00:55,950 --> 00:00:59,440
Thought poison is 0% right thinking.

13
00:00:59,551 --> 00:01:02,561
It is 100% wrong thinking.

14
00:01:03,231 --> 00:01:09,440
And contrary to lots of opinion, women have no exclusive franchise on gossip.

15
00:01:09,551 --> 00:01:14,641
Every day, many men, too, live in a partially poisoned environment.

16
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:24,240
Every day thousands of gossip fests staged by men take place on such topics as the boss's marital or financial problems,

17
00:01:24,511 --> 00:01:30,321
Bill's politicking to get ahead in business, the probability of John being transferred,

18
00:01:30,511 --> 00:01:36,801
the reasons for special favors being awarded Tom, and why they brought in that new man.

19
00:01:37,231 --> 00:01:39,281
Gossiping goes something like this.

20
00:01:39,551 --> 00:01:41,440
Say, I just heard.

21
00:01:41,871 --> 00:01:42,960
No, why?

22
00:01:43,391 --> 00:01:45,361
Well, it doesn't surprise me.

23
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:47,200
He had it coming to him.

24
00:01:47,631 --> 00:01:50,000
Of course, this is confidential.

25
00:01:51,151 --> 00:01:55,121
Conversation is a big part of our psychological environment.

26
00:01:55,311 --> 00:01:57,200
Some conversation is healthy.

27
00:01:57,231 --> 00:01:58,561
It encourages you.

28
00:01:58,831 --> 00:02:03,681
It makes you feel like you're taking a walk in the warm sunshine of a spring day.

29
00:02:03,871 --> 00:02:06,881
Some conversation makes you feel like a winner.

30
00:02:07,391 --> 00:02:12,641
But other conversation is more like walking through a poisonous radioactive cloud.

31
00:02:12,671 --> 00:02:17,440
It chokes you, it makes you feel ill, it turns you into a loser.

32
00:02:18,111 --> 00:02:25,521
Gossip is just negative conversation about people, and the victim of thought poison begins to think he enjoys it.

33
00:02:25,791 --> 00:02:30,960
He seems to get a form of poisoned joy from talking negatively about others,

34
00:02:31,071 --> 00:02:37,281
not knowing that to successful people, he is becoming increasingly unlikable and unreliable.

35
00:02:38,111 --> 00:02:45,281
One of these thought poison addicts walked into a conversation some friends and I were having about Benjamin Franklin.

36
00:02:45,631 --> 00:02:54,641
As soon as Mr. Killjoy learned the topic of our chat, he came through with choice bits about Franklin's personal life in a negative way.

37
00:02:54,991 --> 00:03:01,521
Perhaps it's true that Franklin was a character in some ways, and he might have made the scandal magazines,

38
00:03:01,551 --> 00:03:04,081
had they been around in the 18th century.

39
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:10,240
But the point is, Benjamin Franklin's personal life had no bearing on the discussion at hand,

40
00:03:10,351 --> 00:03:15,681
and I couldn't help being glad that we weren't discussing somebody whom we knew intimately.

41
00:03:16,671 --> 00:03:18,161
Talk about people?

42
00:03:18,271 --> 00:03:21,041
Yes, but stay on the positive side.

43
00:03:21,631 --> 00:03:23,521
Let's make one point clear.

44
00:03:23,710 --> 00:03:24,161
Not all conversation is gossip.
